<item>
            <title>[LU-19545] FLR-EC: Tight binding between erasure code and parity mirrors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19545</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Parity/EC mirrors&lt;/b&gt; need to be tightly coupled to the specific &lt;b&gt;data mirror&lt;/b&gt; they were created to match; otherwise, they cannot provide proper redundancy due to mismatches in stripe_size, stripe_count, component extent, or possibly overlapping OST selection. If they are not linked, the stripe allocation will not correspond correctly between data and parity components and may result in data loss if an OST object is unavailable and EC data recovery is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To accomplish this, we must &lt;b&gt;store the mirror ID of the data mirror&lt;/b&gt; in each of the corresponding parity components.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need &lt;b&gt;16 bits&lt;/b&gt; to represent the mirror ID. To accommodate this, we&#8217;ve selected the &lt;b&gt;LLC timestamp field&lt;/b&gt;, which is currently a 64-bit field that is set and printed but not actually used for functional purposes. We can &lt;b&gt;repurpose the upper 16 bits&lt;/b&gt; of this field to store the &lt;b&gt;mirror ID&lt;/b&gt; of the data mirror associated with each parity mirror.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
